d 'KAPETANIOS': module to perform Kapetanios (2005) unit-root test with up to 5 structural breaks
d
d  kapetanios implements Kapetanios' (2005) unit root test. The
d main advantage of this procedure is that it allows for up to 5
d structural breaks, with break dates endogenously estimated from
d the data. Under the alternative hypothesis of trend stationarity,
d these breaks may occur in the level and/or trend of the series.
d To reflect this, three model specifications are available:
d intercept breaks only (Model A), trend breaks only (Model B), and
d both intercept and trend breaks (Model C, the default), each with
d tabulated critical values. The test regression augments the
d standard ADF equation with structural break dummies and lagged
d differences of the dependent variable to control for serial
d correlation. To determine the appropriate lag length, kapetanios
d supports four selection methods: the sequential t-test of Ng and
d Perron (1995) as used in the original paper (default), a
d Breusch-Godfrey LM test based general-to-specific (GTS)
d procedure, AIC, and BIC. For the AIC and BIC methods, a
d post-selection Breusch-Godfrey test is automatically performed
d and a warning is issued if autocorrelation remains. 
d
d KW: unit root test
d KW: Kapetanios
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260410
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur ,  AHBV University, Ankara, Turkiye
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
f kapetanios.ado
f kapetanios.sthlp
